I, Mr. Ramesh Kumar Sharma, S/o Mohan Lal Sharma, aged 48 years,
residing at 12-A, Hiran Magri, Udaipur – 313 001,
Project Manager, M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd.,
do hereby solemnly affirm and state as follows:

1. I am the Project Manager for the Hospital Construction Project at Udaipur under Work Order
   No. RMSCL/2024-25/Works/4782 and am fully conversant with the facts stated herein.

2. The Work Order was issued on 05.05.2024. As per contract, RMSCL was required to hand over
   the site within 15 days (by 20.05.2024). However, RMSCL gave possession only on 20.05.2024.
   [Note: This date requires factual verification — please confirm the actual delay days from
   site possession certificate before filing.]

3. I personally deployed full resources (150 workers, JCB ×2, concrete mixer ×4, tower crane ×1)
   at the site boundary from 10.05.2024 in anticipation of timely possession.

4. All resources remained idle due to delay in handing over possession, causing direct financial loss.

5. The running bills (RA Bills 3 to 9) submitted by our company aggregating ₹12.45 Crore have
   remained unpaid for over 7 months despite repeated demands.

6. The Structural drawings for Block C were not supplied by RMSCL for 90 days (October to December 2025),
   forcing all Block C construction activities to halt completely.

7. All facts stated above are within my personal knowledge and are true to the best of my information
   and belief. No part of it is false and nothing material has been concealed.

